org.turbogwt.core.http.client

Interface FluentRequestSender<RequestType,ResponseType>

  • Type Parameters:
    RequestType - Type of data to be sent in the HTTP request body, when appropriate.
    ResponseType - Type of result from requests, when appropriate.
    All Superinterfaces:
    FluentRequest<RequestType,ResponseType>, HasUriParts, RequestSender<RequestType,ResponseType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FluentRequestImpl

    public interface FluentRequestSender<RequestType,ResponseType>
extends FluentRequest<RequestType,ResponseType>, RequestSender<RequestType,ResponseType>
    This class provides fluent style request building and sending capabilities.
    Author:
    Danilo Reinert

      • timeout

        FluentRequestSender<RequestType,ResponseType> timeout(int timeoutMillis)
        Sets the number of milliseconds to wait for a request to complete. Should the request timeout, the RequestCallback.onError(com.google.gwt.http.client.Request, Throwable) method will be called on the callback instance given to the RequestBuilder.sendRequest(String, com.google.gwt.http.client.RequestCallback) method. The callback method will receive an instance of the RequestTimeoutException class as its Throwable argument.
        Parameters:
        timeoutMillis - number of milliseconds to wait before canceling the request, a value of zero disables timeouts
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the timeout value is negative

      • on

        FluentRequestSender<RequestType,ResponseType> on(int statusCode,
                                               SingleCallback callback)
        Set a callback to handle specific HTTP status code response.

        The informed code can represent a group of codes, e.g. 4 will handle any code in [400,499]. Similarly, 20 will handle any code in [200,209].

        The codes have priority for specificity, e.g. 201 has a higher priority than 20, which has a higher priority than 2.

        Parameters:
        statusCode - the unit, dozen or hundred expected on response's status code.
        callback - the callback to handle informed code
